OL,3,CUK Athletics boss defends shock
OL,4,Cdecision to include CJ Ujah in GB
OL,5,Crelay squad
OL,7,FThe boss of UK Athletics has defended
OL,8,Fthe shock decision to include sprinter
OL,9,FCJ Ujah in Britain's squad for next
OL,10,Fmonth's World Athletics relays.
OL,12,FMr Ujah failed a drugs test which lead
OL,13,Fto Team GB's 4x100m relay team being
OL,14,Fstripped of its silver medal at the
OL,15,F2020 Tokyo Olympics.
OL,17,FHe subsequently served a 22-month ban
OL,18,Ffor taking a contaminated supplement.
